# Rust Testing

- Add unit tests for new business logic and bug fixes.
- Cover at least one happy path and one failure path for critical use cases.
- Prefer deterministic tests with explicit setup and assertions.
- Keep integration tests focused on behavior, not internal implementation details.
- When tests are not feasible, explain the reason and provide manual verification steps.
